6 1. In all criminal cases except infractions, upon a plea or finding of guilt, the court shall
7 impose a court administration fee in lieu of the assessment of court costs. The court
8 administration fee must include a fee of one hundred twenty-five dollars for a class B
9 misdemeanor, two hundred dollars for a class A misdemeanor, four hundred dollars for
10 a class C felony, six hundred fifty dollars for a class B felony, and nine hundred dollars
11 for a class A or AA felony.
12 2. In addition, in all criminal cases except infractions, the court administration fee must
13 includethe court shall impose an indigent defense and court facilities fee of one
14 hundred dollars. Of the additional one hundred dollar court administration fee, the first
15 seven hundred fifty thousand dollars collected per biennium must be deposited in the
16 indigent defense administration fund, which must be used for indigent defense
17 services in this state, and the next four hundred sixty thousand dollars collected per
18 biennium must be deposited in the court facilities improvement and maintenance fund.
19 After the minimum thresholds have been collected, one-half of the additional court
20 administration fee must be deposited in each fund.
21 3. In addition to any court administration fees that may be imposed under subsections 1
22 and 2, the court shall impose upon each defendant who receives a sentence that
23 includes community service a community service supervision fee of twenty-five dollars.
24 The community service supervision fee must be deposited in the community service
25 supervision fund. The fees deposited in this fund must be used to provide community
26 service supervision grants subject to legislative appropriations.
